# http://w3id.org/opino/describes
<http://w3id.org/opino/describes> <http://www.w3.org/1999/02/22-rdf-syntax-ns#type> <http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#ObjectProperty> .
<http://w3id.org/opino/describes> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#subPropertyOf> <http://www.ontologydesignpatterns.org/ont/dul/DUL.owl#describes> .
<http://w3id.org/opino/describes> <http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#inverseOf> <http://w3id.org/opino/isDescribedBy> .
<http://w3id.org/opino/describes> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#domain> <http://w3id.org/opino/Opinion> .
<http://w3id.org/opino/describes> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#range> <http://www.ontologydesignpatterns.org/ont/dul/DUL.owl#Entity> .
<http://w3id.org/opino/describes> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#comment> "Relates an Opinion to the entity its propositional content is about — the subject of the claim."@en .
<http://w3id.org/opino/describes> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#isDefinedBy> "http://w3id.org/opino/"^^<http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema#anyURI> .
<http://w3id.org/opino/describes> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#label> "describes"@en .
# 
# http://w3id.org/opino/enables
<http://w3id.org/opino/enables> <http://www.w3.org/1999/02/22-rdf-syntax-ns#type> <http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#ObjectProperty> .
<http://w3id.org/opino/enables> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#subPropertyOf> <http://www.ontologydesignpatterns.org/ont/dul/DUL.owl#hasPostcondition> .
<http://w3id.org/opino/enables> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#domain> <http://w3id.org/opino/Construal> .
<http://w3id.org/opino/enables> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#range> <http://w3id.org/opino/Construal> .
<http://w3id.org/opino/enables> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#comment> "Relates a Construal to another Construal that it makes possible as a subsequent step in an inferential chain. A Construal enables another when it provides the evidential or logical basis from which the subsequent Construal can be constituted. For example, the Construal 'Fief is a Medieval Latin term' enables the Construal 'The Donation contains anachronistic Latin', which in turn grounds the Opinion 'The Donation is a Forgery'. Inverse counterpart of opino:presupposes in the inferential chain, though not declared as a formal OWL inverse. Subproperty of dul:hasPostcondition."@en .
<http://w3id.org/opino/enables> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#isDefinedBy> "http://w3id.org/opino/"^^<http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema#anyURI> .
<http://w3id.org/opino/enables> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#label> "enables"@en .
# 
# http://w3id.org/opino/grounds
<http://w3id.org/opino/grounds> <http://www.w3.org/1999/02/22-rdf-syntax-ns#type> <http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#ObjectProperty> .
<http://w3id.org/opino/grounds> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#subPropertyOf> <http://www.ontologydesignpatterns.org/ont/dul/DUL.owl#satisfies> .
<http://w3id.org/opino/grounds> <http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#inverseOf> <http://w3id.org/opino/isPremisedOn> .
<http://w3id.org/opino/grounds> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#domain> <http://w3id.org/opino/Construal> .
<http://w3id.org/opino/grounds> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#range> <http://w3id.org/opino/Opinion> .
<http://w3id.org/opino/grounds> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#comment> "Relates a Construal to the Opinion it supports as premises support a conclusion. Inverse of opino:isPremisedOn. Subproperty of dul:satisfies, preserving full DnS semantics."@en .
<http://w3id.org/opino/grounds> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#isDefinedBy> "http://w3id.org/opino/"^^<http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema#anyURI> .
<http://w3id.org/opino/grounds> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#label> "grounds"@en .
# 
# http://w3id.org/opino/hasEpistemicRegion
<http://w3id.org/opino/hasEpistemicRegion> <http://www.w3.org/1999/02/22-rdf-syntax-ns#type> <http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#ObjectProperty> .
<http://w3id.org/opino/hasEpistemicRegion> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#subPropertyOf> <http://www.ontologydesignpatterns.org/ont/dul/DUL.owl#hasRegion> .
<http://w3id.org/opino/hasEpistemicRegion> <http://www.w3.org/1999/02/22-rdf-syntax-ns#type> <http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#FunctionalProperty> .
<http://w3id.org/opino/hasEpistemicRegion> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#domain> <http://w3id.org/opino/EpistemicStatusParameter> .
<http://w3id.org/opino/hasEpistemicRegion> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#range> <http://w3id.org/opino/EpistemicRegion> .
<http://w3id.org/opino/hasEpistemicRegion> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#comment> "Relates an EpistemicStatusParameter to the EpistemicRegion individual that represents its value in the epistemic quality space. Functional because each EpistemicStatusParameter is valued by exactly one EpistemicRegion at any given time. Subproperty of dul:hasRegion, scoped to opino:EpistemicStatusParameter as domain and opino:EpistemicRegion as range."@en .
<http://w3id.org/opino/hasEpistemicRegion> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#isDefinedBy> "http://w3id.org/opino/"^^<http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema#anyURI> .
<http://w3id.org/opino/hasEpistemicRegion> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#label> "has epistemic region"@en .
# 
# http://w3id.org/opino/hasEpistemicStatus
<http://w3id.org/opino/hasEpistemicStatus> <http://www.w3.org/1999/02/22-rdf-syntax-ns#type> <http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#ObjectProperty> .
<http://w3id.org/opino/hasEpistemicStatus> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#subPropertyOf> <http://www.ontologydesignpatterns.org/ont/dul/DUL.owl#hasParameter> .
<http://w3id.org/opino/hasEpistemicStatus> <http://www.w3.org/1999/02/22-rdf-syntax-ns#type> <http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#FunctionalProperty> .
<http://w3id.org/opino/hasEpistemicStatus> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#domain> <http://w3id.org/opino/Opinion> .
<http://w3id.org/opino/hasEpistemicStatus> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#range> <http://w3id.org/opino/EpistemicStatusParameter> .
<http://w3id.org/opino/hasEpistemicStatus> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#comment> "Relates an Opinion to the parameter that carries its current epistemic status value. Functional because each Opinion has exactly one epistemic status at any given time."@en .
<http://w3id.org/opino/hasEpistemicStatus> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#isDefinedBy> "http://w3id.org/opino/"^^<http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema#anyURI> .
<http://w3id.org/opino/hasEpistemicStatus> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#label> "has epistemic status"@en .
# 
# http://w3id.org/opino/hasPart
<http://w3id.org/opino/hasPart> <http://www.w3.org/1999/02/22-rdf-syntax-ns#type> <http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#ObjectProperty> .
<http://w3id.org/opino/hasPart> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#subPropertyOf> <http://www.ontologydesignpatterns.org/ont/dul/DUL.owl#hasPart> .
<http://w3id.org/opino/hasPart> <http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#inverseOf> <http://w3id.org/opino/isPartOf> .
<http://w3id.org/opino/hasPart> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#domain> <http://w3id.org/opino/Construal> .
<http://w3id.org/opino/hasPart> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#range> <http://www.ontologydesignpatterns.org/ont/dul/DUL.owl#Situation> .
<http://w3id.org/opino/hasPart> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#comment> "Relates a Construal to its constituent sub-situations, each representing an individual premise as perceived by the cognizer. The relation is recursive — a sub-Situation may itself have parts that ground it further, mirroring the CRMinf premise chain (J1 usedAsPremise). Each sub-Situation may optionally satisfy a dul:Description (e.g. a Framester frame), representing the inference logic (CRMinf J3 applies) through which that premise is interpreted. The conclusion drawn from the full Construal is always an opino:Opinion (dul:Description), connected via opino:grounds."@en .
<http://w3id.org/opino/hasPart> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#isDefinedBy> "http://w3id.org/opino/"^^<http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema#anyURI> .
<http://w3id.org/opino/hasPart> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#label> "has part"@en .
# 
# http://w3id.org/opino/heldBy
<http://w3id.org/opino/heldBy> <http://www.w3.org/1999/02/22-rdf-syntax-ns#type> <http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#ObjectProperty> .
<http://w3id.org/opino/heldBy> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#subPropertyOf> <http://www.ontologydesignpatterns.org/ont/dul/DUL.owl#associatedWith> .
<http://w3id.org/opino/heldBy> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#domain> <http://w3id.org/opino/Opinion> .
<http://w3id.org/opino/heldBy> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#range> <http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#Thing> .
<http://w3id.org/opino/heldBy> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#comment> "Shortcut property relating an opino:Opinion directly to the agent who holds it. Equivalent to navigating opino:Opinion --prov:wasGeneratedBy--> prov:Activity --prov:wasAssociatedWith--> prov:Agent. Retained for querying convenience."@en .
<http://w3id.org/opino/heldBy> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#isDefinedBy> "http://w3id.org/opino/"^^<http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema#anyURI> .
<http://w3id.org/opino/heldBy> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#label> "held by"@en .
# 
# http://w3id.org/opino/holdsAtTime
<http://w3id.org/opino/holdsAtTime> <http://www.w3.org/1999/02/22-rdf-syntax-ns#type> <http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#ObjectProperty> .
<http://w3id.org/opino/holdsAtTime> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#subPropertyOf> <http://www.ontologydesignpatterns.org/ont/dul/DUL.owl#includesTime> .
<http://w3id.org/opino/holdsAtTime> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#domain> <http://w3id.org/opino/Construal> .
<http://w3id.org/opino/holdsAtTime> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#range> <http://www.ontologydesignpatterns.org/ont/dul/DUL.owl#TimeInterval> .
<http://w3id.org/opino/holdsAtTime> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#comment> "Relates a TimeIndexedConstrual to the TimeInterval during which the construed state of affairs holds. A TimeIndexedConstrual represents a perspective-dependent set of facts that are valid only within a specific temporal bound — this property makes that bound explicit. For example, the attribution of a painting to the School of Caravaggio as perceived by the Zeri Foundation holds during the interval 1990–2005."@en .
<http://w3id.org/opino/holdsAtTime> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#isDefinedBy> "http://w3id.org/opino/"^^<http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema#anyURI> .
<http://w3id.org/opino/holdsAtTime> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#label> "holds at time"@en .
# 
# http://w3id.org/opino/involves
<http://w3id.org/opino/involves> <http://www.w3.org/1999/02/22-rdf-syntax-ns#type> <http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#ObjectProperty> .
<http://w3id.org/opino/involves> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#subPropertyOf> <http://www.ontologydesignpatterns.org/ont/dul/DUL.owl#isSettingFor> .
<http://w3id.org/opino/involves> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#domain> <http://w3id.org/opino/Construal> .
<http://w3id.org/opino/involves> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#range> <http://www.ontologydesignpatterns.org/ont/dul/DUL.owl#Entity> .
<http://w3id.org/opino/involves> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#comment> "Relates a Construal to any entity — object, agent, event, or abstract concept — that the cognizer perceives as participating in the construed state of affairs. Following the social psychology notion of construal (Ross 1987), the entities involved are not neutral facts but are perceived and interpreted through the cognizer's subjective lens. The Construal grounds the Opinion (subclass of Description)."@en .
<http://w3id.org/opino/involves> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#isDefinedBy> "http://w3id.org/opino/"^^<http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema#anyURI> .
<http://w3id.org/opino/involves> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#label> "involves"@en .
# 
# http://w3id.org/opino/isDescribedBy
<http://w3id.org/opino/isDescribedBy> <http://www.w3.org/1999/02/22-rdf-syntax-ns#type> <http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#ObjectProperty> .
<http://w3id.org/opino/isDescribedBy> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#subPropertyOf> <http://www.ontologydesignpatterns.org/ont/dul/DUL.owl#isDescribedBy> .
<http://w3id.org/opino/isDescribedBy> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#domain> <http://www.ontologydesignpatterns.org/ont/dul/DUL.owl#Entity> .
<http://w3id.org/opino/isDescribedBy> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#range> <http://w3id.org/opino/Opinion> .
<http://w3id.org/opino/isDescribedBy> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#comment> "Inverse of opino:describes."@en .
<http://w3id.org/opino/isDescribedBy> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#isDefinedBy> "http://w3id.org/opino/"^^<http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema#anyURI> .
<http://w3id.org/opino/isDescribedBy> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#label> "is described by"@en .
# 
# http://w3id.org/opino/isPartOf
<http://w3id.org/opino/isPartOf> <http://www.w3.org/1999/02/22-rdf-syntax-ns#type> <http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#ObjectProperty> .
<http://w3id.org/opino/isPartOf> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#subPropertyOf> <http://www.ontologydesignpatterns.org/ont/dul/DUL.owl#isPartOf> .
<http://w3id.org/opino/isPartOf> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#domain> <http://w3id.org/opino/Construal> .
<http://w3id.org/opino/isPartOf> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#range> <http://w3id.org/opino/Construal> .
<http://w3id.org/opino/isPartOf> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#comment> "Inverse of opino:hasPart"@en .
<http://w3id.org/opino/isPartOf> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#isDefinedBy> "http://w3id.org/opino/"^^<http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema#anyURI> .
<http://w3id.org/opino/isPartOf> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#label> "is part of"@en .
# 
# http://w3id.org/opino/isPremisedOn
<http://w3id.org/opino/isPremisedOn> <http://www.w3.org/1999/02/22-rdf-syntax-ns#type> <http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#ObjectProperty> .
<http://w3id.org/opino/isPremisedOn> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#subPropertyOf> <http://www.ontologydesignpatterns.org/ont/dul/DUL.owl#isSatisfiedBy> .
<http://w3id.org/opino/isPremisedOn> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#domain> <http://w3id.org/opino/Opinion> .
<http://w3id.org/opino/isPremisedOn> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#range> <http://w3id.org/opino/Construal> .
<http://w3id.org/opino/isPremisedOn> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#comment> "Relates an Opinion to the Construal that constitutes its premises — the set of facts as perceived by the cognizer from which the Opinion results as a conclusion. Subproperty of dul:isSatisfiedBy, preserving full DnS semantics."@en .
<http://w3id.org/opino/isPremisedOn> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#isDefinedBy> "http://w3id.org/opino/"^^<http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema#anyURI> .
<http://w3id.org/opino/isPremisedOn> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#label> "is premised on"@en .
# 
# http://w3id.org/opino/perceivedBy
<http://w3id.org/opino/perceivedBy> <http://www.w3.org/1999/02/22-rdf-syntax-ns#type> <http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#ObjectProperty> .
<http://w3id.org/opino/perceivedBy> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#subPropertyOf> <http://www.ontologydesignpatterns.org/ont/dul/DUL.owl#associatedWith> .
<http://w3id.org/opino/perceivedBy> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#domain> <http://w3id.org/opino/Construal> .
<http://w3id.org/opino/perceivedBy> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#range> <http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#Thing> .
<http://w3id.org/opino/perceivedBy> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#comment> "Relates a Construal to the cognizer whose perspective constitutes it. Shortcut for: grounds inverse → Opinion → prov:wasGeneratedBy → Activity → prov:wasAssociatedWith → Agent."@en .
<http://w3id.org/opino/perceivedBy> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#isDefinedBy> "http://w3id.org/opino/"^^<http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema#anyURI> .
<http://w3id.org/opino/perceivedBy> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#label> "perceived by"@en .
# 
# http://w3id.org/opino/presupposes
<http://w3id.org/opino/presupposes> <http://www.w3.org/1999/02/22-rdf-syntax-ns#type> <http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#ObjectProperty> .
<http://w3id.org/opino/presupposes> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#subPropertyOf> <http://www.ontologydesignpatterns.org/ont/dul/DUL.owl#hasPrecondition> .
<http://w3id.org/opino/presupposes> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#domain> <http://w3id.org/opino/Construal> .
<http://w3id.org/opino/presupposes> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#range> <http://w3id.org/opino/Construal> .
<http://w3id.org/opino/presupposes> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#comment> "Relates a Construal to another Construal  that must hold as a logical premise before it. Represents the inferential ordering between premise Construals in a chain of reasoning — the 'presupposed' Construal provides the evidential or logical ground that the dependent Construal builds upon. For example, the Construal 'Fief is a Medieval Latin term' is the presupposition of the Construal 'The Donation contains anachronistic Latin'. Subproperty of dul:hasPrecondition, defined in DUL as direct precedence applied to situations."@en .
<http://w3id.org/opino/presupposes> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#isDefinedBy> "http://w3id.org/opino/"^^<http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema#anyURI> .
<http://w3id.org/opino/presupposes> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#label> "presupposes"@en .
# 
# http://w3id.org/opino/usesConcept
<http://w3id.org/opino/usesConcept> <http://www.w3.org/1999/02/22-rdf-syntax-ns#type> <http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#ObjectProperty> .
<http://w3id.org/opino/usesConcept> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#subPropertyOf> <http://www.ontologydesignpatterns.org/ont/dul/DUL.owl#usesConcept> .
<http://w3id.org/opino/usesConcept> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#domain> <http://w3id.org/opino/Opinion> .
<http://w3id.org/opino/usesConcept> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#range> <http://www.ontologydesignpatterns.org/ont/dul/DUL.owl#Concept> .
<http://w3id.org/opino/usesConcept> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#comment> "Relates an Opinion to the concept being predicated of its subject. "@en .
<http://w3id.org/opino/usesConcept> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#isDefinedBy> "http://w3id.org/opino/"^^<http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema#anyURI> .
<http://w3id.org/opino/usesConcept> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#label> "uses concept"@en .
# 
