<http://w3id.org/opino/TimeIndexedConstrual> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#comment> "A Construal where the perceived state of affairs holds only during a specific time interval. Inherits from both opino:Construal — carrying the perspectival and epistemic properties of a perception — and dul:TimeIndexedRelation, which provides the temporal bounding mechanism. Used when the perceived premises are not timeless observations but temporally bounded states of affairs, such as attributions, classifications, or roles that held only during a specific period."@en .
<http://w3id.org/opino/TimeIndexedConstrual> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#isDefinedBy> "http://w3id.org/opino/"^^<http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema#anyURI> .
<http://w3id.org/opino/TimeIndexedConstrual> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#label> "Time-Indexed Construal"@en .
